comments: Dinwiddie's (BKN) hand slides off of Murray's (ATL) off-arm and the contact that occurs during the driving shot attempt is marginal.
Johnson's (BKN) hand slides off of Young's (ATL) front and releases away without applying pressure as Young splits between two defenders.
Murray (ATL) cleanly deflects the ball from Thomas (BKN), any ensuing contact while pursuit of the loose ball is consider incidental.
Thomas (BKN) makes hand-on-ball contact with Murray (ATL) during his drive toward the rim. Any ensuing contact after the ball is dislodged is incidental.
Thomas (BKN) traps the ball to the backboard while defending the shot attempt.
Bey (ATL) moves alongside Bridges' (BKN) path and absorbs the contact initiated by Bridges during the driving shot attempt.
Johnson (BKN) steps laterally into Young's (ATL) path and initiates contact with his lower body which affects his SQBR as he is dribbling the ball up the floor.
Dinwiddie (BKN) does not bring his hand underneath the ball as he makes a move toward the rim.
Murray's (ATL) off-arm arm comes toward Thomas' (BKN) arm, and he releases away without applying pressure during his drive toward the rim
Thomas (BKN) briefly rests his hand on Murray's (ATL) front during Murray's drive toward the rim.
Dinwiddie (BKN) rests his hand on Bogdanovic's (ATL) side and releases away without applying pressure as Bogdanovic sets the pick.
Finney-Smith (BKN) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Bey (ATL) avoids initiating contact with Johnson's (BKN) arm as he is contesting the jump shot.
Bridges (BKN) momentarily rests his hand on Young's (ATL) front and releases away without applying pressure as he contests Young's drive toward the rim.
Dinwiddie (BKN) gets to ball height and avoids initiating contact with Young (ATL) as he contests the shot attempt.
